Infographic: What makes Delhi an economic giant among states? 
9-3-2017 
What makes Delhi an economic giant among states?

Though Delhi is the smallest state of India, it outranks giants like Punjab, Haryana and Kerala in GDP and its per capita income is now the highest in the country. These six charts show how it compares with other states on several parameters and why it is a trailblazer of sorts. 
